1 state building code.
2 (F) Must require that lands not be rezoned following the site’s inclusion within the urban
3 growth boundary for a period of:
4 (i) Thirty years for manufactured dwelling parks; or
5 (ii) Twenty years for manufactured dwellings or prefabricated structures.
6 SECTION 3. Section 57, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, as amended by section 3, chapter 341,
7 Oregon Laws 2025, and section 7, chapter 530, Oregon Laws 2025, is amended to read:
8 Sec. 57. (1) Within 21 days after the adoption of an amendment to an urban growth boundary
9 or the adoption or amendment of a conceptual plan under sections 49 to 59, chapter 110, Oregon
10 Laws 2024, and the approval by a county if required under section 50 (2), chapter 110, Oregon Laws
11 2024, the conceptual plan or amendment must be submitted to the Department of Land Conservation
12 and Development for review. The submission must be made by:
13 (a) The city, for an amendment under section 50 or 58, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, [or]
14 section 2, chapter 341, Oregon Laws 2025, or section 2 of this 2026 Act [of this 2025 Act]; or
15 (b) Metro, for an amendment under section 51 or 58, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, or section
16 2 of this 2026 Act.
17 (2) Within 60 days after receiving a submittal under subsection (1) of this section, the depart-
18 ment shall:
19 (a) Review the submittal for compliance with the provisions of sections 49 to 59, chapter 110,
20 Oregon Laws 2024.
21 (b)(A) If the submittal substantially complies with the provisions of sections 49 to 59, chapter
22 110, Oregon Laws 2024, issue an order approving the submittal; or
23 (B) If the submittal does not substantially comply with the provisions of sections 49 to 59,
24 chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, issue an order remanding the submittal to the city or to Metro with
25 a specific determination of deficiencies in the submittal and with sufficient detail to identify a spe-
26 cific remedy for any deficiency in a subsequent resubmittal.
27 (3) If a conceptual plan is remanded to Metro under subsection (2)(b) of this section:
28 (a) The department shall notify the city; and
29 (b) The city may amend its conceptual plan and resubmit a petition to Metro under section 51,
30 chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024.
31 (4) Judicial review of the department’s order:
32 (a) Must be as a review of orders other than a contested case under ORS 183.484; and
33 (b) May be initiated only by the city or an owner of a proposed site that was submitted to the
34 department.
35 (5) Following the approval of a submittal under this section, a local government must include
36 the added lands in any future inventory of buildable lands or determination of housing capacity
37 under ORS 197A.270, 197A.280, 197A.335 or 197A.350.
38 SECTION 4. Section 60, chapter 110, Oregon Laws 2024, as amended by section 4, chapter 341,
39 Oregon Laws 2025, is amended to read:
